The paper proposes a framework for predicting transportation modes from GPS traces using feature engineering and noise removal. This involves data preparation, point and trajectory feature extraction, and normalization. The approach involves the use of classifiers and empirical tests to evaluate the performance of the framework. Given the focus on machine learning and data analysis, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
